File: Various South African political leaders present in the National Assembly. JOHANNESBURG - The National Assembly will debate the country's unemployment crisis on Thursday.
DA leader Mmusi Maimane asked the Parliament Speaker Thandi Modise for an urgent debate on joblessness. WATCH: SA's unemployment rate now at 29% The country's unemployment rate climbed to 29-percent in the second quarter of the year. DA leader Mmusi Maimane asked the Speaker for an urgent debate on joblessness. Courtesy #DStv403 Maimane says the DA will use the debate to table its comprehensive economic recovery plan. WATCH: Ramaphosa on the unemployment rate He says the debate should address unsustainable levels of government spending. These include the bailing out of debt-ridden and failing state-owned entities and cutting the Public Sector Wage Bill.